---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Tickr Privacy Policy">
  <main class="relative min-h-screen overflow-hidden px-4 pb-20 pt-24 text-white sm:pt-28">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_top,_#111827_0%,_#0f172a_50%,_#020617_100%)]"></div>
    <div class="absolute -left-40 top-24 h-72 w-72 rounded-full bg-sky-500/20 blur-[140px]"></div>
    <div class="absolute right-10 top-40 h-64 w-64 rounded-full bg-indigo-500/20 blur-[160px]"></div>

    <Navbar />

    <div class="mx-auto mt-10 w-full max-w-3xl space-y-10">
      <header class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-white/50">Tickr</p>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold sm:text-4xl">Privacy policy</h1>
        <p class="text-base text-white/70">
          Tickr keeps your salary amounts and income sources stored locally on your device using secure
          storage. We do not sell or share your personal earnings data. Anonymous analytics may be
          collected to improve the app, such as crash diagnostics and basic usage patterns.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/60">Last updated: December 2025</p>
        <a
          href="/"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-white/20 bg-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold text-white/80 transition hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:text-white"
        >
          ‚Üê Back to home
        </a>
      </header>

      <section class="space-y-4 rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Data we store on your device</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/70">
          Salary figures, income sources, and related details you enter in Tickr are saved on your device
          using the platform's secure storage. This information does not leave your device unless you
          choose to share or back it up through your operating system.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/70">
          <li>We do not run our own servers for your salary data, and we do not require you to create an account.</li>
          <li>You control what you enter and can remove it by clearing entries in the app or uninstalling Tickr.</li>
          <li>
            If you use device-level backups (iCloud, Google device backup, etc.), your data may be included in
            those backups under the provider's terms; we do not access it.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Analytics and diagnostics</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/70">
          We collect anonymous analytics to understand app reliability and performance. These events help
          prioritize fixes and improvements.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/70">
          <li>Crash reports and error logs (e.g., app version, device type, operating system, and error codes).</li>
          <li>Basic usage signals (e.g., screens viewed, feature usage counts, session length) without salary amounts.</li>
          <li>
            Analytics are processed in aggregate and are not linked to your salary data or personal contact details.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Data sharing &amp; selling</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/70">
          <li>We do not sell your personal earnings data.</li>
          <li>We do not share salary or income entries with advertisers or third parties.</li>
          <li>
            Anonymous analytics and crash diagnostics may be processed by service providers solely to operate
            and improve the app.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Security</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/70">
          <li>Salary data is stored using platform-secure storage mechanisms on your device.</li>
          <li>Protect access to your device with a passcode or biometrics and keep your operating system updated.</li>
          <li>If your device is lost or compromised, remove data by wiping the device or uninstalling Tickr.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Your choices</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/70">
          <li>Review, edit, or delete the salary and income information you have entered at any time.</li>
          <li>Delete the app to remove locally stored data from your device.</li>
          <li>
            For privacy questions or to report a concern, contact us at
            <a class="text-white/90 hover:text-white" href="mailto:hello@fieldcraftlabs.dev">
              hello@fieldcraftlabs.dev
            </a>.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/70">
          We may update this policy to reflect changes in Tickr or applicable regulations. When updates are made,
          we will revise the date above. Continued use of the app after an update signifies acceptance of the
          revised policy.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
